    "kernel": "5.1.9-arch1-1-ARCH",
    "notes": "Tested under Arch Linux on 2019-07-04 and works flawlessly with Proton 4.2.\n\nFor those of you getting the DirectX 11 feature 10 required error, this is how to fix it:\n\n- cd ~/.steam/steam/steamapps/common/Proton 4.2 (or whatever your latest Proton version is)\n- cp user_settings.sample.py user_settings.py\n- Now edit user_settings.py with your favorite editor\n- Uncomment the line: \"PROTON_USE_WINED3D\": \"1\", (remove the # at the beginning of the line)\n\nAs that line's description says, it forces OpenGL-based wined3d for d3d11 and d3d10 instead of Vulkan-based DXVK\n\nI have an AMD Radeon R9 290 and I'm now able to play this game at 1080p @ 60 FPS.\n\nHope this helps someone!",
